{"body": "```\r\nshould not be up to the project to tell the developer how to conform his/her development environment\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the common case, it really should be, though. Most apps will \"just work\" with shared, uniform dev config. That's a good thing!\r\n\r\nFor those who need specialized per-developer config, I'd first question why. For it's own sake? Because each dev env is a unique snowflake? Probably not. However, if it really is needed, then go ahead and axe the uniform config. That should be a pretty high bar.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/5629973", "created_at": "2012-05-10T16:35:58Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6210#issuecomment-5629973", "updated_at": "2012-05-10T16:35:58Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6210, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jeremy", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/24d2f8804e6bb4b7ea6bd11e0a586470?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F84d9ee44e457ddef7f2c4f25dc8fa865.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/received_events", "gravatar_id": "24d2f8804e6bb4b7ea6bd11e0a586470", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jeremy", "type": "User", "id": 199, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52380c97bd3543c15100d192"}, "id": 5629973, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6210"}
